  ('gyve','g','dʒaiv',ARRAY['n.','v.','vt.'],'[{"pos": "", "en": "H () the eighth letter of the English alphabet, is classed among the", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "consonants, and is formed with the mouth organs in the same position as", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "that of the succeeding vowel. It is used with certain consonants to", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "form digraphs representing sounds which are not found in the alphabet,", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "as sh, th, /, as in shall, thing, /ine (for zh see /274); also, to", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "modify the sounds of some other letters, as when placed after c and p,", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "with the former of which it represents a compound sound like that of", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "tsh, as in charm (written also tch as in catch), with the latter, the", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "sound of f, as in phase, phantom. In some words, mostly derived or", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "introduced from foreign languages, h following c and g indicates that", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "those consonants have the hard sound before e, i, and y, as in", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "chemistry, chiromancy, chyle, Ghent, Ghibelline, etc.; in some others,", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "ch has the sound of sh, as in chicane. See Guide to Pronunciation, //", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "", "en": "153, 179, 181-3, 237-8.", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "n.", "en": "A shackle; especially, one to confine the legs; a fetter.", "zh": "脚镣, 手铐"}, {"pos": "v.", "en": "t. To fetter; to shackle; to chain.", "zh": ""}, {"pos": "vt.", "en": "", "zh": "使上脚镣, 使上手铐"}]','[]',0,'',ARRAY['gyves']),
